Based on my analysis of the Frontend Utilities subsystem files, I've identified several potential bugs and security vulnerabilities:

```json
{
  "issues": [
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/app/directives/external-link.directive.ts",
      "line": 41,
      "description": "Null/undefined URL vulnerability - if both currentTarget and target are null or don't have href attributes, url will be null/undefined, causing OpenExternalLink to fail"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/app/pipes/filter.pipe.ts",
      "line": 30,
      "description": "Potential null reference exception - accessing it[field] without checking if 'field' property exists on the object"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/app/pipes/dataset-latest-entry.pipe.ts",
      "line": 40,
      "description": "Potential null reference exception - calling toString() on lastItemValue without null check, could crash if lastItemValue is null/undefined"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/app/pipes/safe-html.pipe.ts",
      "line": 12,
      "description": "XSS security vulnerability - bypassSecurityTrustHtml bypasses Angular's sanitization without input validation, allowing arbitrary HTML/script injection"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/app/pipes/safe-html.pipe.ts",
      "line": 14,
      "description": "XSS security vulnerability - bypassSecurityTrustScript bypasses Angular's sanitization, allowing arbitrary script execution"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/lib/utils/external_link.ts",
      "line": 8,
      "description": "Undefined global variable - 'wails' is accessed without checking if it exists globally, could cause ReferenceError in non-desktop environments"
    },
    {
      "file": "frontend/src/lib/utils/uuid.ts",
      "line": 4,
      "description": "Potential browser compatibility issue - crypto.getRandomValues may not be available in all environments/older browsers"
    }
  ]
}
